For babywearing questions, comment below or email advice@sollybaby.com and Morgan would be happy to assist. 💛

node.text:
Our Fauna hat (👈🏽) is sold out, but we still have a few Forget-Me-Knot hats (👉🏽) left, so now's the perfect time to grab one if you've had your eye on it! 🌿 These tiny toppers are designed for birth to 6 months, with an adjustable knot and roll-up bottom so babe can wear them at the hospital all the way up to their half birthday.✨ 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
P.S. Neutral Stripe (in the middle!) is part of our classic collection, so it'll be sticking around. 🤗

node.text: If you're in the thick of postpartum and spending your days trying to figure out just who this little person is and what all their many cries might mean and if/how/when you'll ever sleep again, let this 👆🏽 bring you hope. In what will one day seem like the blink of an eye, you'll be sharing inside jokes and too-wet kisses, and they'll know you're their person and you'll know they're the best thing that ever happened to you, and you'll fit together in your favorite spot just the way you always have, but with a little more certainty, a little more confidence, and maybe, just maybe, a little more rest. 💕@lily_jieru

node.text: And once you embrace this, it's LIBERATING. 🙌🏼 The shift in expectations changes *everything* and suddenly you're not annoyed that you haven't read a single chapter of your novel📗 or slept past 7 am💤 (or 5:30 am🤪) but instead thrilled that you're rocking baby to sleep listening to the waves of a real ocean🌊 (that don't come from a sound machine! 😂) or pulling over to change a diaper in the back of the car with jaw-dropping mountains⛰ as the backdrop, or simply picking up carryout🍱 from somewhere other than your neighborhood pizza joint🍕 that you've ordered from 100x in the past year. It's all about perspective, you know? ✨

node.text:
When mamas ask how many wraps they need…
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I always recommend two—one print + one solid. ✌🏽 The print makes even a basic tee feel pulled together; the solid goes with literally everything. And most importantly, having a second means you’re not in a bind when baby has a blowout 💩 and you have to toss one in the wash midday. Bc we’ve ALL been there, amirite? 🙋🏽‍♀️
